{
  "buggy_files": ["net/sunrpc/sched.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["__rpc_execute"],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "The bug is in the __rpc_execute function at net/sunrpc/sched.c:783-792. When a synchronous RPC task receives a fatal signal while waiting for a reply (via out_of_line_wait_on_bit), the code immediately calls rpc_exit(task, -ERESTARTSYS) without first checking if the RPC reply has already been received (rq_reply_bytes_recvd). The bug report shows that tcpdump captures the server's reply arriving successfully, but the client returns -512 (ERESTARTSYS) anyway. This is because the signal interrupts the wait loop before xprt_complete_rqst() is called to set rq_reply_bytes_recvd, and the code at line 792 unconditionally exits with the signal error. The fix should check req->rq_reply_bytes_recvd before calling rpc_exit() - if bytes have been received, the task should continue to decode the reply rather than returning the signal error."
}

